Anybody else like to kick doors down like me in the name of Jesus?

20:00.396 --> 20:03.280
I at least do it in the name of Jesus, right?

20:04.241 --> 20:07.005
Jesus is here, right?

20:07.025 --> 20:09.929
Nothing good happens on the other side of me kicking those doors down.

20:12.672 --> 20:16.978
I wonder, could our waiting be the presence of God's love rather than the absence of it?

20:19.650 --> 20:23.875
You see, waiting is for glory and waiting is for love, but all waiting has another purpose.

20:23.895 --> 20:27.119
And here's what we learn in the waiting is that all waiting is for growth.

20:28.060 --> 20:29.983
The disciples are gonna learn this lesson right now.

20:30.023 --> 20:34.849
And John chapter 11 verse 14 says this, then Jesus told them plainly, Lazarus has died.

20:34.889 --> 20:38.033
And if I'm one of the disciples, I'm like, yeah, cause you waited.

20:39.595 --> 20:44.941
Jesus walked on water, couldn't go help your boy, right?

20:44.961 --> 20:46.483
Yeah, he's dead.

20:46.523 --> 20:48.786
And Jesus says,

20:49.186 --> 20:56.034
And for your sake, the disciples now, for your sake, I am glad that I was not there.

20:56.915 --> 21:01.780
So that you may believe, but let us go to him.

21:02.942 --> 21:08.128
You see, this waiting isn't just for Lazarus to be raised or to show his glory and love for his friends.

21:08.428 --> 21:13.874
That's what we can sometimes get narrow minded and think that all our waiting is just to teach us a lesson.

21:14.082 --> 21:17.909
It wasn't just to teach Mary, Martha, Lazarus and all the other crowd a lesson.

21:18.169 --> 21:24.881
It was teaching the disciples something to get them ready so that when he died and rose from the grave, they could do the mission that God had for them.

21:25.102 --> 21:28.187
They were going to wait and wait and wait and wait and wait.

21:28.568 --> 21:30.391
They were going to suffer and suffer and suffer.

21:30.411 --> 21:36.562
And so right here, he's like, I'm glad that I wasn't there because you need to believe.

21:37.666 --> 21:46.077
The waiting was to grow the belief of the disciples who would be the sent ones to start the church, to spread the gospel, to make disciples, and to change the world.

21:46.318 --> 21:47.980
And the same thing is true of us.

21:48.861 --> 21:50.423
If he's just 210, tell us it is.

21:50.663 --> 21:56.411
For we, we, not I, not me, we together, are his workmanship.

21:57.232 --> 22:04.562
Created in Christ Jesus for good works which God prepared beforehand that we together should walk in them.

22:04.642 --> 22:07.807
I don't wanna miss, there's a little theological thing here that is so powerful.

22:07.847 --> 22:10.491
This word, workmanship, is this word, potema.

22:10.972 --> 22:11.773
And here's what it means.

22:12.094 --> 22:14.778
It means that we are his craftsmanship.

22:14.998 --> 22:16.921
We are his masterpiece.

22:17.221 --> 22:20.987
We are his something intentionally formed.

22:21.929 --> 22:26.856
Right now, God in your life is trying to intentionally form you into a person of love.

22:27.117 --> 22:30.141
He is trying to intentionally form you into the image of his son.

22:30.442 --> 22:33.106
And if you're like me, that is really hard work.

22:34.306 --> 22:35.988
He's got to carve a lot of stuff off.

22:36.209 --> 22:37.731
He's got to chisel a lot of things.

22:37.931 --> 22:41.417
He's got to do a lot of inner man and inner woman work, right?

22:41.717 --> 22:45.823
We clean up the outside and he's like, dude, I'm just getting started, right?

22:46.364 --> 22:47.746
The porn, the addiction, all that.

22:47.806 --> 22:49.248
That was just the easy stuff.

22:49.288 --> 22:51.932
Wait until we get into the thoughts and intentions of the heart.

22:52.833 --> 22:56.319
We gonna have to wait because that's gonna take some time.

22:56.359 --> 22:59.343
That's gonna take some work, but we are his masterpiece.

22:59.363 --> 23:02.187
That's why he does this work.

23:03.349 --> 23:04.050
I want you to,

23:04.514 --> 23:06.637
Apply this to your mind and your heart.

23:07.038 --> 23:10.543
We are not self-improvement projects.

23:10.964 --> 23:13.608
We are divine formation.

23:13.628 --> 23:23.784
I think some of us come to the Word of God and we come to the presence of God and we come to church and we're like, here's where I'm just going to get a little better.

23:23.804 --> 23:30.514
No, this is where I get formed by the divine hand of God.

23:32.130 --> 23:34.373
That's why I come into the secret place.

23:34.393 --> 23:36.475
That's why you go into the prayer room.

23:36.495 --> 23:46.307
That's why you come up to encounter guides and say, man, I need God to do a deep work inside my heart because you are a divine formation.

23:46.327 --> 23:48.449
A. W. Toes said, God never hurries.

23:49.290 --> 23:51.893
There are no deadlines against which he must work.

23:53.395 --> 23:59.602
And we as Christians need to extend that to other Christians, other people, other lost people.

24:00.322 --> 24:03.926
God doesn't have a timeline on when you have to be like him at a certain place.

24:04.947 --> 24:06.228
He's chiseling away.

24:06.268 --> 24:07.430
He's using your weighting.

24:07.470 --> 24:08.931
He's using your suffering.

24:08.951 --> 24:11.274
But sometimes we're like, man, you haven't gotten it yet?

24:12.475 --> 24:13.596
You haven't been baptized yet?

24:13.636 --> 24:14.597
What are you waiting for?

24:15.518 --> 24:16.540
Man, God's doing a work.

24:16.640 --> 24:17.200
Let him do it.

24:18.221 --> 24:18.802
Let him do it.

24:20.344 --> 24:21.785
Jesus was never governed.

24:23.007 --> 24:25.609
Know this if you're waiting, especially if you're waiting and suffering.

24:26.330 --> 24:29.874
Jesus was never governed by urgency, sickness,

24:30.114 --> 24:30.935
or even death.

24:32.859 --> 24:33.640
We fear death.

24:35.202 --> 24:39.109
It's while we pray when someone gets cancer that they will be healed and not die.

24:40.752 --> 24:42.555
Jesus was not afraid of Lazarus death.

24:43.396 --> 24:46.000
And I don't believe it was just because he knew he could raise him from the dead.

24:46.221 --> 24:47.423
Jesus was not afraid of death.

24:48.124 --> 24:49.286
He was never afraid of death.

24:49.967 --> 24:50.548
Not for a second.

24:50.728 --> 24:54.955
I think he was afraid of being separated from his father by becoming sin for us, but not afraid of death.

24:55.476 --> 24:56.658
Those are two separate things.

24:56.866 --> 25:02.357
When you've been with God the Father for eternity, it's a little scary to spend three days separated from Him and He came and look at you.

25:04.181 --> 25:06.946
Sanctification, sanctification of my friends takes time.

25:07.267 --> 25:09.050
Renewing the mind takes time.

25:09.311 --> 25:11.796
Knowledge, wisdom, discernment takes time.

25:13.980 --> 25:14.962
Takes time.

25:16.482 --> 25:19.666
Impacting and changing the identity of a city takes time.

25:20.007 --> 25:24.433
I got here in 2020, and one of the first things I learned was the good old mantra, right?

25:24.673 --> 25:25.234
Peoria.

25:25.254 --> 25:26.236
It's not that bad.

25:30.181 --> 25:33.285
That's the worst mantra in any city's history, right?

25:33.305 --> 25:35.228
It's worse than Sin City in Vegas.

25:35.468 --> 25:37.331
At least they got it right, right?

25:38.072 --> 25:40.195
Peoria's better than it's not that bad.

25:41.316 --> 25:42.418
It's better than that.

25:44.418 --> 25:50.204
But it takes time to change the self view of a city.

25:52.026 --> 25:53.968
It takes a long time to change a culture.

25:54.849 --> 25:57.472
Creating culture based upon kingdom values takes time.

25:58.053 --> 26:00.215
Planting churches that revive community, guess what?

26:00.715 --> 26:01.496
It takes time.

26:02.457 --> 26:07.022
God planted a seed in us to plant a church in the East Bluff almost five years ago.

26:07.263 --> 26:08.404
And it's still not open.

26:08.864 --> 26:10.546
Brian, what's taken so long?

26:14.146 --> 26:14.587
I don't know.

26:15.668 --> 26:20.236
It takes time experiencing your overflow.

26:21.157 --> 26:21.698
What's it take?

26:23.501 --> 26:23.881
Time.

26:24.562 --> 26:25.804
You're still not interactive yet.

26:25.824 --> 26:27.647
We're working on it.

26:27.667 --> 26:28.328
Thank you, Brian.

26:29.290 --> 26:30.211
It takes time.

26:30.251 --> 26:32.976
It takes waiting.

26:35.239 --> 26:36.181
But the good news is this.

26:37.102 --> 26:38.003
Don't miss the good news.

26:38.785 --> 26:39.666
That's where I started.

26:41.954 --> 26:44.237
If you're waiting, hasn't produced the glory of God yet.

26:44.878 --> 26:47.641
If you haven't yet been loved by God in your waiting.

26:48.762 --> 26:52.367
If you like, man haven't gotten a place where the waiting is growing you.

26:52.447 --> 26:55.371
Here's the good news to Corinthians chapter nine verse eight.

26:57.413 --> 26:57.954
God is able.

27:00.597 --> 27:05.002
You may be here this morning, I have hated every second of the waiting that God has made me do.

27:05.263 --> 27:05.823
God is able.

27:06.744 --> 27:07.986
God is able to change your heart.

27:08.322 --> 27:10.285
God is able to change your mindset with waiting.

27:10.505 --> 27:12.828
God is able to change your mindset with the suffering.

27:12.848 --> 27:14.190
God is able to change your life.

27:14.210 --> 27:17.594
Man, you're like, man, I've been struggling with faith in God for years.

27:17.694 --> 27:19.637
I still never have heard his voice.

27:19.877 --> 27:20.478
God is able.

27:21.319 --> 27:21.860
God is able.

27:22.160 --> 27:23.943
Maybe you haven't pursued him enough.

27:24.023 --> 27:25.364
Maybe you haven't drawn close enough.

27:25.425 --> 27:26.746
Maybe you haven't surrendered enough.

27:26.907 --> 27:28.729
I don't know what it is, but God is able.

27:28.789 --> 27:30.411
And what is he able to do in your waiting?

27:30.712 --> 27:32.594
Make all grace abound to you.

27:32.898 --> 27:43.217
so that having all sufficiency in all things at all times, you and I may abound in every good work.

27:45.901 --> 27:49.127
Don't waste our waiting.

27:51.652 --> 27:55.218
Mary and Martha are going to see a resurrection.

27:56.802 --> 28:02.950
Lazarus is going to end up being one of the few men in the history of the world that can say I was dead, not came back, y'all.

28:06.495 --> 28:16.628
The disciples got to take another step in their belief so they became the world changers that God wanted them to be.

28:18.951 --> 28:24.658
Instead of trying to get out of your waiting, maybe today God could just lead you and say, why am I waiting?

28:26.306 --> 28:27.768
How can I glorify you?

28:28.388 --> 28:32.153
How can I receive it as love from a father?

28:33.615 --> 28:39.382
And how can I grow to be more like the image you originally created me to be?

28:41.204 --> 28:49.394
I'm gonna invite Pastor Marty up and he's gonna lead us into a time of encounter as we just heard God's word.

28:49.414 --> 28:49.714
Marty?

